he represents

39:03.920 --> 39:05.800
some sort of early

39:05.800 --> 39:07.260
pre-Egyptian,

39:07.500 --> 39:09.340
pre-Pythagorean Druidism

39:09.340 --> 39:10.640
taking place

39:10.640 --> 39:11.740
not just in Ireland,

39:11.900 --> 39:12.700
not just in Wales,

39:12.800 --> 39:13.760
but certainly in Scotland

39:13.760 --> 39:15.320
and he confects

39:15.320 --> 39:17.020
this entire sort of

39:17.020 --> 39:18.800
early Druid republic

39:18.800 --> 39:19.440
where everything

39:19.440 --> 39:20.180
is godly

39:20.180 --> 39:21.620
and virtuous.

39:22.860 --> 39:23.440
We've missed

39:23.440 --> 39:24.280
our human sacrifice

39:24.280 --> 39:24.900
and we haven't got

39:24.900 --> 39:25.300
much time.

39:25.380 --> 39:26.140
We've got to turn to it

39:26.140 --> 39:26.740
because it's part

39:26.740 --> 39:27.300
of the story.

39:27.500 --> 39:29.040
They were accused of,

39:29.080 --> 39:29.260
well,

39:29.440 --> 39:29.960
there's been human

39:29.960 --> 39:30.900
sacrifice in so many

39:30.900 --> 39:31.700
religions and they

39:31.700 --> 39:32.140
continue.

39:33.700 --> 39:34.180
Can you,

39:34.380 --> 39:35.660
and it was thought

39:35.660 --> 39:36.860
by some early writers

39:36.860 --> 39:37.960
and some early commentators,

39:38.040 --> 39:39.040
was this black propaganda

39:39.040 --> 39:39.560
that Miranda

39:39.560 --> 39:40.280
you're going to tell us,

39:40.600 --> 39:41.880
as being excessive,

39:42.120 --> 39:43.540
that altars ran with blood,

39:43.740 --> 39:44.620
that sort of thing.

39:44.860 --> 39:46.000
What about human sacrifice

39:46.000 --> 39:46.620
and the Druids?

39:46.660 --> 39:47.180
What do we know?

39:48.540 --> 39:49.780
I think it's fair to say

39:49.780 --> 39:50.700
that human sacrifice

39:50.700 --> 39:51.960
probably did take place.

39:52.100 --> 39:52.480
There is some

39:52.480 --> 39:53.200
archaeological evidence

39:53.200 --> 39:53.780
for it,

39:53.920 --> 39:54.320
for example,

39:54.380 --> 39:55.060
in the bog bodies

39:55.060 --> 39:56.420
places like Lindo Moss

39:56.420 --> 39:57.300
that I've mentioned before

39:57.300 --> 39:58.340
and quite a lot

39:58.340 --> 39:59.240
of other evidence

39:59.240 --> 40:00.700
but the archaeological

40:00.700 --> 40:01.940
evidence suggests

40:01.940 --> 40:03.060
that it was happening

40:03.060 --> 40:04.060
but it was rare

40:04.060 --> 40:05.340
and it would only happen

40:05.340 --> 40:06.440
at times of great crisis

40:06.440 --> 40:07.860
and I think what's happened

40:07.860 --> 40:09.620
is that when Caesar

40:09.620 --> 40:10.340
talks about it,

40:10.400 --> 40:11.060
he talks about it

40:11.060 --> 40:12.220
in a very matter-of-fact way.

40:12.860 --> 40:15.240
He says it is,

40:15.600 --> 40:16.300
the Druids find it

40:16.300 --> 40:18.060
appropriate to sacrifice

40:18.780 --> 40:19.700
human beings

40:19.700 --> 40:22.120
for efficacious purposes.

40:22.680 --> 40:23.460
They would try and use

40:23.460 --> 40:24.140
prisoners of war

40:24.140 --> 40:24.600
or criminals

40:24.600 --> 40:25.280
but if there weren't

40:25.280 --> 40:25.580
enough

40:25.580 --> 40:26.520
then the innocents

40:26.520 --> 40:27.320
would make up

40:27.320 --> 40:27.740
the numbers.

40:28.480 --> 40:29.060
He's very pragmatic

40:29.060 --> 40:29.640
about this.

40:29.860 --> 40:30.540
We have to remember

40:30.540 --> 40:31.860
that human sacrifice

40:31.860 --> 40:33.440
was only outlawed

40:33.440 --> 40:34.700
in Rome in 97 BC,

40:34.880 --> 40:35.860
not that long ago

40:35.860 --> 40:36.960
before Caesar.

40:37.660 --> 40:38.620
The other writers

40:38.620 --> 40:39.240
like Pliny,

40:39.400 --> 40:39.920
like Tacitus,

40:40.060 --> 40:40.580
like Lucan,

40:40.820 --> 40:41.660
they do sort of

40:41.660 --> 40:43.580
talk it up a bit.

40:43.700 --> 40:44.460
They do talk about

40:44.460 --> 40:45.460
altars running with blood

40:45.460 --> 40:47.360
but I think human sacrifice

40:47.360 --> 40:48.300
did take place

40:48.300 --> 40:49.080
but it was not

40:49.080 --> 40:50.660
that out of the ordinary.

40:50.820 --> 40:51.240
It was not

40:51.240 --> 40:52.980
that big a deal.

40:52.980 --> 40:53.580
Barry?

40:53.940 --> 40:54.340
Barry Conner?

40:54.520 --> 40:54.760
Yes,

40:54.900 --> 40:56.140
there is evidence

40:56.140 --> 40:58.400
in Iron Age archaeology

40:58.400 --> 41:00.440
that bodies,

41:00.700 --> 41:02.200
people were sacrificed

41:02.200 --> 41:02.640
I think.

41:03.200 --> 41:04.720
I excavated some pits

41:04.720 --> 41:05.540
in a hill fort

41:05.540 --> 41:06.180
called Dainbury

41:06.180 --> 41:08.560
where there are bodies

41:08.560 --> 41:10.380
thrown into the bottoms

41:10.380 --> 41:10.960
of pits

41:10.960 --> 41:11.940
with stones

41:11.940 --> 41:12.980
heaped down on them.

41:13.080 --> 41:14.080
Now that doesn't look

41:14.080 --> 41:15.040
very much like

41:15.040 --> 41:16.260
normal burial practice

41:16.260 --> 41:18.240
so there are hints

41:18.240 --> 41:18.760
like that

41:18.760 --> 41:19.840
in the archaeological evidence

41:19.840 --> 41:20.840
and indeed

41:20.840 --> 41:21.560
the bog bodies

41:21.560 --> 41:22.660
